habitat_description: Tringa incana is found along the Pacific coast of conterminous U.S. during spring and fall migration as well as during the winter (Gill et al., 2002). During the winter, the species uses rocky intertidal shorelines (Grinnell and Miller, 1944; DeSante and Ainley, 1980; Townsend, 1968; Bradley and Bradley, 1993; Wootton, 1997; Morrison et al., 2000; Gill et al., 2002), including jetties (Bowles, 1932).
